items.name: BottomInset
lines: specifies the inset from the bottom.
The inset is the distance between the outer and the inner window, that means the bottom inset is the height of the bottom border.

items.name: Height
lines: specifies the outer (total) height of the window.

items.name: LeftInset
lines: specifies the inset from the left.
The inset is the distance between the outer and the inner window, that means the left inset is the width of the left border.

items.name: RightInset
lines: specifies the inset from the right.
The inset is the distance between the outer and the inner window, that means the right inset is the width of the right border.

items.name: TopInset
lines: specifies the inset from the top.
The inset is the distance between the outer and the inner window, that means the top inset is the height of the top border.

items.name: Width
lines: specifies the outer (total) width of the window.

items.name: X
lines: specifies the outer x position of the window.

items.name: Y
lines: specifies the outer y position of the window.
